node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Keep On Learning on September 14, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Bank that lost 66 workers on 9/11 has paid for all their kids to go to college UNILAD'.

node.text:
On 11th September, 2001, 66 men and women working for the investment banking firm Sandler O’Neill & Partners on the 104th floor in the World Trade Center lost their lives in the terror attack.

The company decided to set up a foundation to pay for the 76 children of those employees to go to college. 20 years on, 54 of those children have had their college education paid for and another 22 remain eligible.

The youngest among them is now a 19-year-old who was born just six weeks after September 11th. When they graduate from college, the Sandler O'Neill Foundation will cease to exist in all ways but the memory of the victims and the lasting education of their children.

Via: @unilad
